[center]
[color=#ffff00][size=6][b]Simple Location Manager[/b][/size][/color]
[i]Save, Organise, and Share your favourite spots in Night City.[/i][/center]
[line]
[color=#ffff00][size=5][b]Overview[/b][/size][/color]
Ever found a preem photo spot, a hidden gem, or a great testing location, only to lose it forever? [b]Simple Location Manager[/b] is a UI tool for Cyber Engine Tweaks that lets you save, organise, and share locations with ease.

[b]Simple Location Manager[/b] is designed for organisation first. It automatically detects your location, identifying the District and sub-district, and organises your locations into a clean, collapsible hierarchy.

[color=#ffff00][size=4][b]New in v1.1.0[/b][/size][/color]
[list]
[*][b]Custom Categories:[/b] create, edit, and share your own categories with unique custom icons.
[*][b]AMM Support:[/b] import Appearance Menu Mod locations. 
[*][b]Presets:[/b] support for installing location packs with auto-installing categories.
[/list]
[color=#ffff00][size=5][b]Key Features[/b][/size][/color]
[list]
[*][b]Save Anywhere:[/b] Instantly record your position. Add custom names, descriptions, or let the mod auto-timestamp them.
[*][b]Smart Organisation:[/b] Locations are automatically grouped by [b]District[/b] or [b]Category[/b].
[*][b]Favorites:[/b] Keep your most-used spots at the top of the list for instant access.
[*][b]Custom Categories (New):[/b] Create your own categories (e.g., "Stunts", "Photos") and assign them unique icons.
[*][b]AMM Support (New):[/b] Import existing locations created for Appearance Menu Mod. [i]AMM is [b]not[/b] required for this to work.[/i] 
[*][b]Powerful Search:[/b] Filter by name, district, or description in real-time.
[*][b]Import / Export:[/b] Share locations with your choombas! Copy a single spot, a whole district, or your entire database to the clipboard as a text string.
[*][b]Navigation:[/b] One-click to set a [b]Custom Map Pin[/b] to any saved location. [i]Works great with Autodrive![/i]
[*][b]Lazy Mode (Teleport):[/b] Optional feature to instantly teleport to any saved spot (Disabled by default).
[*][b]Customizable:[/b][list]
[*]Adjust duplicate warning distance.
[*]Choose if groups start Expanded or Collapsed.
[*]Toggle extra UI details like raw coordinates.
[*]Group locations by [b]District [/b]or [b]Category[/b].
[/list]
[/list][line]
[color=#ffff00][size=5][b]Installation[/b][/size][/color]
[b]Requirements:[/b]
[url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/107]Cyber Engine Tweaks[/url] (Latest Version)

[b]How to Install:[/b]
[list=1]
[*] Download the mod.
[*] Extract the [font=Courier New]bin[/font] folder to your Cyberpunk 2077 root directory.
[i]*Final Path should look like:* [font=Courier New]Cyberpunk 2077\bin\x64\plugins\cyber_engine_tweaks\mods\SimpleLocationManager\[/font][/i]
[/list]
[line]
[color=#ffff00][size=5][b]Usage[/b][/size][/color]
[list=1]
[*] Open the CET Overlay (chosen during CET install).
[*] The [b]Simple Location Manager[/b] window will appear.
[*] Click [b]"+"[/b] to save your current spot.
[/list]
[line]
[color=#ffff00][size=5][b]For Mod Authors: Create Presets[/b][/size][/color]
Want to publish a list of locations? (Hidden gems, photo spots, stash houses?)
[b]Simple Location Manager[/b] supports [b]Presets[/b] that allow you to distribute locations easily.

[list]
[*]Create a [font=Courier New].txt[/font] file with your exported locations.
[*]Users simply install your mod with the preset file in the [font=Courier New]presets[/font] folder, and it will automatically show in the locations list.
[*][b]Custom Categories Auto-Install:[/b] If you use a custom category (e.g., "My Stash" with a specific icon), it will [b]automatically be created[/b] for the user when they load your preset. No manual setup required!
[/list]
[url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/articles/1960][b]Read the full guide on creating Presets here[/b][/url]
[line]
[color=#ffff00][size=5][b]Import / Export[/b][/size][/color]
To export a location, click on the export button on the location. A simple code string will be added to your clipboard. This can be pasted for easy sharing/backup.
Importing a location is as simple as pasting that export string into the import window found under the settings tab.

[color=#ffff00][size=4][b]Import from AMM[/b][/size][/color]
You can now import existing Appearance Menu Mod locations!
[b][i]AMM is not required to be installed for this to work.
[/i][/b]
[list]
[*][b]Bulk Import (For Appearance Menu Mod):[/b]
[list=1]
[*]Install the AMM location mod as per the mod's instructions. [i](Remember to endorse it!)[/i]
[*]Copy the .json files from the AMM folder:
[font=Courier New]bin\x64\plugins\cyber_engine_tweaks\mods\AppearanceMenuMod\User\Locations[/font]
to the SLM import folder:
[font=Courier New]bin\x64\plugins\cyber_engine_tweaks\mods\SimpleLocationManager\import[/font]
[*]Load the game, open SLM &gt; Settings Tab &gt; Import Button &gt; "AMM Bulk Import" tab.
[*]Click "Scan Directory & Import".
[/list][/list]
[list][*][b]Manual Import:[/b] Simply paste the content from any AMM JSON file into the import box, and it will be automatically detected and converted.
[/list]
[color=#ffff00][size=4][b]SLM Export Strings[/b][/size][/color]
These strings can be shared with other users of the mod, or as a way to back up your list of locations (Export all button in the settings tab).

Here are some examples that you can import to get started. [b][i]Check out the Forum posts for more locations as they get added![/i][/b]

