[line]
[color=#ffff00][size=5][b]Hints / Tips[/b][/size][/color]
[list]
[*]You can set a keybind in the [b]CET bindings[/b] to "[b]Quicksave[/b]" a location to return to without interrupting your gameplay.
[*]All the buttons have a tooltip when you hover over them to see what they do
[*]Check the [b]Settings[/b] tab to [b]enable Lazy Mode[/b] (Teleport) or adjust UI preferences.
[*]Right-click any district or category header to [b]Export[/b] it.
[*]You can get the coordinates for your current location using the "Print Coordinates" button in the settings tab.
[list][*]This outputs the coordinates to the CET Console.
[*]This does [i]not[/i] add the current location to the list.
[/list][*]The [b]Dump District Info [/b]button will output your current district and subdistrict details to the console and the mods .log file
[list][*]This is useful for debugging purposes
[/list][/list]
[line]
[color=#ffff00][size=5][b]Known issues[/b][/size][/color]
[list]
[*]The breadcrumb trail for the custom mappin is not automatically generated. [i]This is a vanilla game limitation[/i]. Opening/closing the map will generate them for you.
[/list]
